Project-6¶

Domain : Material Manufacturing¶

Description : Concrete is the most important material in civil engineering. The concrete compressive strength is a highly nonlinear function of age and ingredients. These ingredients include cement, blast furnace slag, fly ash, water, superplasticizer, coarse aggregate, and fine aggregate

The data has 8 quantitative input variables, and 1 quantitative output variable, and 1030 instances (observations)

def outlier_cnt_low_high(df, col_name):
    df_low_outlier = 0 
    df_high_outlier = 0
    msg = ""
    q1 = df[col_name].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = df[col_name].quantile(0.75)
    iqr = q3-q1 #Interquartile range
    fence_low  = q1-1.5*iqr
    fence_high = q3+1.5*iqr
    df_low_outlier = df[col_name].loc[(df[col_name] < fence_low)].count()
    df_high_outlier = df[col_name].loc[(df[col_name] > fence_high)].count()
    
    if df_low_outlier > 0 and df_high_outlier > 0 :
        msg = "Both Low and Upper Outlier exists"
    elif df_low_outlier == 0 and df_high_outlier == 0 :
        msg = "No outliers exists"
    elif df_low_outlier > 0 and df_high_outlier == 0 :
        msg = "Only lower limit outlier exists"
    elif df_low_outlier == 0 and df_high_outlier > 0 :
        msg = "Only upper limit outlier exists"

    return df_low_outlier, df_high_outlier, msg

### Uni-variate analysis which includes (name, range of values, central values (mean/median), standard deviation, quartiles, 
### analysis of the body of distribution / tails, missing values, ouliers)
def univariate_analysis(df, col_name):
    
    low_cnt, upper_cnt, msg = outlier_cnt_low_high(df, col_name)
    
    analysisDF = pd.DataFrame({'column':col_name.upper(), 
                               'min_value':df[col_name].min(), 
                               'max_value':df[col_name].max(), 
                               'mean':df[col_name].mean(), 
                               'median':df[col_name].median(), 
                               'std':df[col_name].std(), 
                               '25th_quartile':df[col_name].quantile(.25), 
                               '50th_quartile':df[col_name].quantile(.50), 
                               '75th_quartile':df[col_name].quantile(.75), 
                               'skew_tails':df[col_name].skew(), 
                               'missing_val':df[col_name].isnull().values.any(), 
                               'outliers':msg},index=[0])
    print (analysisDF)

def age_category(conDF):
    if conDF['age'] <= 30:
        return '1 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 30 and conDF['age'] <= 60:
        return '2 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 60 and conDF['age'] <= 90:
        return '3 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 90 and conDF['age'] <= 120:
        return '4 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 120 and conDF['age'] <= 150:
        return '5 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 150 and conDF['age'] <= 180:
        return '6 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 180 and conDF['age'] <= 210:
        return '7 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 210 and conDF['age'] <= 240:
        return '8 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 240 and conDF['age'] <= 270:
        return '9 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 270 and conDF['age'] <= 300:
        return '10 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 300 and conDF['age'] <= 330:
        return '11 Month'
    if conDF['age'] > 330:
        return '12 Month'
    
conDF["age_in_months"] = conDF.apply(lambda conDF:age_category(conDF) , axis=1)

In [60]:
def regression_scores(ypredict):
    mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, ypredict)
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_true=y_test, y_pred=ypredict)
    rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, ypredict))
    r2 = r2_score(y_test, ypredict)
    
    return mse, mae, rmse, r2
In [61]:
result_df = pd.DataFrame()
def result(method, scr, mse, mae, rmse, r2):
    global result_df
    temp_result = pd.DataFrame({'Method':method, 
                            'Score':scr, 
                            'MSE':mse,
                            'MAE':mae,
                            'RMSE':rmse, 
                            'R Squared':r2},index=[0])
    result_df = pd.concat([result_df, temp_result])

## Using PCA 
cov_matrix = np.cov(X_features, rowvar=False)

np.linalg.eig(cov_matrix)

eigenvalues, eigenvectors, = np.linalg.eig(cov_matrix)

eig_pairs = [(eigenvalues[index], eigenvectors[:,index]) for index in range(len(eigenvalues))]

# Sort the (eigenvalue, eigenvector) pairs from lowest to highest with respect to eigenvalue
eig_pairs.sort()
eig_pairs.reverse()    # reverses the sorted pairs from increasing value of eigenvalue to lowest

# Extract the descending ordered eigenvalues and eigenvectors
eigvalues_sort = [eig_pairs[index][0] for index in range(len(eigenvalues))]
eigvectors_sort = [eig_pairs[index][1] for index in range(len(eigenvalues))]
In [114]:
tot = sum(eigenvalues)

var_explained = [(i / tot) for i in sorted(eigenvalues, reverse=True)]  # an array of variance explained by each 

cum_var_exp = np.cumsum(var_explained)  # an array of cumulative variance.

cum_var_exp
